    openingLine: 'The shadow does not destroy the man who names it. It destroys the man who never does.',
    teachingBody:
      "Jung used the word *shadow* for the disowned parts of the self — the impulses, hungers, angers, and patterns the conscious mind would prefer not to belong to it. The shadow does not disappear when ignored. It runs the man from underneath, surfacing in the form of compulsions, projections, and unexplained reactivity.\n\nThe practice eventually requires looking at the shadow. Not wallowing in it, not making a religion of it, but seeing it. The man who can name what he has not wanted to see in himself takes back some of the power the unnamed material had over him. What is named loses some of its grip.\n\nThis arc is about that work. The Sage's first task is recognition: there are things in me I have been managing not to look at. They are part of why the compulsion has had purchase. They are also workable, if I can stay with looking.",
    secretContentType: 'hidden_teaching', secretTitle: 'Hidden Teaching',
    secretBody: "The shadow is not evil. It is unintegrated. The angry man who refuses to admit his anger is more dangerous than the angry man who knows what he carries. The compulsive pattern that is denied has more power than the one that is named. Shadow work is not confession. It is intelligence. Once material is named, it becomes available to be worked with rather than reacted from. Begin with one thing you have been managing not to see. One is enough.",
    crownFragment: 'The shadow named is the shadow workable.',
    command: 'Today, name one shadow material honestly. To yourself first. Possibly to one other.',
    practice: 'Sit ten minutes with a difficult inward truth without rushing to resolve it.',
    forgeChallenge: 'Speak one shadow honestly to one trusted person today. Not the worst. The one you are ready to begin with.',
    journalPrompt: 'What in me have I been managing not to look at? Why?',
    eveningAccount: 'Did I see anything in myself today that I usually do not let myself see?',
    seal: 'The shadow named is the shadow workable.',
    contentStatus: 'final',
    relatedStudyIds: [],
    relatedPrincipleIds: ['lapse-is-information', 'man-is-never-enemy'],
    milestoneRiteId: null,
    safetyGuardrail: 'This is philosophical and psychological inspiration, not a substitute for professional support.',
