    teachingBody:
      "The intelligence gathered through honest shadow work has one main use: it tells the man where the next boundary needs to be. Pre-lapse boundaries are guesses. Post-lapse boundaries are informed by data. They tend to be more specific, more targeted, more effective.\n\nA boundary is not a moral fence. It is a structural commitment: an environmental change, a time rule, a relational protocol, a piece of physical or digital architecture that makes the unwanted behavior measurably harder to perform on autopilot. \"I will not\" is a boundary. \"I will not, and the phone is in another room from 9 PM, and Tuesday nights I am at the gym, and on Sundays I check in with X\" is a boundary system.\n\nThe Guardian's work in arc 8 is to build these boundaries informed by what the shadow work has revealed. Not from shame. From data.",
    secretContentType: 'night_warning', secretTitle: 'Night Warning',
    secretBody: "The boundaries built in calm daylight, written down with structure, are the boundaries that hold at 11 PM. The boundaries decided in the moment of temptation almost never hold. Treat the building of boundaries as separate work from the keeping of them. Build them when calm. Keep them when tested. The hour of temptation is not the hour to legislate; it is the hour to obey what was already legislated.",
    crownFragment: 'A boundary is law passed when calm and obeyed when tested.',
