    openingLine: 'The desire does not leave. The direction becomes stable.',
    teachingBody:
      "It is important to be honest about what the ninety days do and do not do. They do not produce a man without desire. They do not eliminate appetite. They do not make the body new. The body continues to be the body, with its hungers and its rhythms and its insistent aliveness.\n\nWhat the ninety days can produce is something more useful: stable direction. The desire is still there, but it points somewhere. Toward worthy work. Toward training. Toward real relationships. Toward service. Toward attention itself. The desire is no longer constantly being hijacked by the easiest available outlet because the harder, worthier outlets have become more habitual.\n\nThe Sovereign's truth about the long path: desire never leaves; direction becomes more reliable. That is the equipment the man is being given. It is not the equipment the marketing of \"victory\" suggests. It is better, because it is the equipment that actually works for a life.",
    secretContentType: 'crown_fragment', secretTitle: 'Crown Fragment',
    secretBody: "Eighty-three days. Most men would be celebrating the elimination of desire. The practice does not eliminate it. The practice directs it. This fragment belongs in your Codex: desire with direction is not a problem. It is a life. The man who waits for desire to disappear before he considers himself free will wait forever. The man who lets desire point toward worthy things is free now.",
    crownFragment: 'Desire with direction is not a problem. It is a life.',
