    id: 'day-87', dayNumber: 87, arcNumber: 9, arcTitle: 'The Crown',
    title: 'Teach Without Preaching', theme: 'witness, quiet example, not proselytizing',
    season: 'the_integrated_man', archetype: 'brother',
    invocation: 'Today you walk as the Brother: a man whose changed life teaches more than any sermon he could give.',
    archetypeExpression:
      "The Brother governs today because his loyalty is warm presence, not recruitment — and preaching from a fresh success often signals fragility, the need to convince others to confirm his own conviction. He lives the practice visibly, answers briefly and honestly when asked, and makes no effort to grow a movement. So today's command is restraint: when tempted to explain, live it instead, and be present to someone in a way that communicates without arguing.",
    lineagePassageId: 'synthesis-teach-by-example',
    openingLine: 'The crowned man does not preach. He is present in a way that speaks.',
    teachingBody:
      "After the practice produces real change, the man may be tempted to talk about it. To friends, to family, to anyone who will listen. The temptation is usually well-meant. It is also usually a mistake. Preaching from a position of having just succeeded tends to repel the very people the man hopes to reach. It often signals fragility rather than strength: the man needs to convince others to confirm his own conviction.\n\nThe better path is harder: live the practice visibly without explaining it. Let those who notice ask. Answer briefly and honestly when asked. Make no effort to recruit. The example does the work that argument cannot.\n\nThe Brother's discipline here is restraint. The discipline is for him. Sharing it with others is not the validation he might think it is. The man whose life quietly changes — who is calmer, more reliable, more present — communicates something about the practice that no sermon can.",
    secretContentType: 'hidden_teaching', secretTitle: 'Hidden Teaching',
